Terms of Use for images in the Archives of African American Music and Culture Collections:

The images in this collection are made available under an assertion of fair use (17 U.S.C. 107) and may be used only for non-commercial educational or research purposes. Please contact the AAAMC for permission to publish or otherwise reuse these images. Permission for publication is granted by the AAAMC as the owner of the physical item and is not intended to include or imply permission of the copyright holder. The user is responsible for securing permission from the copyright owner and any other rights holders for any reuse of these images extending beyond fair use or other statutory exemptions. If you are the copyright holder for any of the digitized materials and have questions about its inclusion on our site, please contact the AAAMC staff.
